Sentencas: Power generating characteristics of pressurized anode-supported cell (ASC) and electrolyte-supported cell (ESC) are measured using the same single-cell stack setup, a planar full cell sandwiched by a pair of rib-channel flow distributors.
Titulo: Effects of pressurization and temperature on power generating characteristics and impedances of anode-supported and electrolyte-supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both ASC and ESC apply the same flow rates (Q(node) = 0.5 slpm H-2 + 0.4 slpm N-2 and Q(cathode) = 0.9 slpm air) measured at three operating temperatures (T = 750 degrees C, 800 degrees C, 850 degrees C), each T under five pressures (p = 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 atm), having a total of 30 data sets for comparison.
Titulo: Effects of pressurization and temperature on power generating characteristics and impedances of anode-supported and electrolyte-supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is found that under loaded conditions, ASC has much larger increments in power densities, about three folds higher, than ESC due to pressurization.
Titulo: Effects of pressurization and temperature on power generating characteristics and impedances of anode-supported and electrolyte-supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As T increases from 750 degrees C to 850 degrees C at 0.7 V, power densities of ASCIESC increase from 175/97 mW cm(-2) to 309/193 mW cm(-2) at p = 1 atm, while at p = 5 atm, the increases of power densities are 281/137 mW cm(-2) to 476/250 mW cm(-2), showing a stronger temperature dependence than pressurization.
Titulo: Effects of pressurization and temperature on power generating characteristics and impedances of anode-supported and electrolyte-supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Corresponding electrochemical impedance spectra show that the better cell performance of ASC is attributed to both lower ohmic and polarization resistances found in ASC than that in ESC.
Titulo: Effects of pressurization and temperature on power generating characteristics and impedances of anode-supported and electrolyte-supported planar solid oxide fuel cells
